               <head>Poetry of Fayzi Fayyazi, 4 items (a-d)</head>
               <msContents class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129656 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046">
                  <summary>Collection of poetic compositions in varied forms and genres by the polymath translator, philosopher, Sufi, and poet, Shaykh Abū al-Fayz̤ ibn Shaykh Mubārak Nāgawrī, takhalluṣ Fayz̤ī and Fayyāz̤ī (d. 1004/1595), who was made poet laureate or malik al-shuʿarāʾ in 997/1589 at the court of the Timurid (Mughal) Emperor Akbar I (d. 1014/1605). The colophon to item d refers to the volume as a kullīyāt, however it is not the formal title as the volume is far from comprehensive, lacking the prose works, collection of refined correspondence, and the lengthier poetic compositions making up the poet’s incomplete Khamsah. Volume not dated; items a and d dated (28 November 1829-15 January 1840). Awkward but clear nastaʿlīq. Red and blue jadval rulings. Rudimentary sarlawḥ on folios 1v and 123r. Limited annotations and corrections in margins. Intermittent pencil and regular Persian foliation. Lacking original binding. Detached binding damaged (deep reddish brown leather exterior, pasteboards exposed without doubleurs), labelled. Folios mostly bound, occasional loose leaves; cropped, water stains, limited wormholes, curling edges. Condition poor.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1372-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="121v">ff. 1v-121v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1372a.</p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of Persian and Arabic eulogies or qaṣāʾid, with rubrics, by the poet Fayz̤ī (d. 1004/1595).</p>
                        <p>The work commences with the poet’s own biographical preface in refined prose.</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 121v): completed morning of 28 Navambar (November) 1829 ʿĪsavī.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656359.0x000001 viaf_1363149296267380670008">Fayz̤ī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_1363149296267380670008">فيضى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1372-item2">
                     <locus from="123r" to="333v">ff. 123r-333v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_1363149296267380670008">Fayz̤ī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_1363149296267380670008">فيضى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1372b.</p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of Persian and Arabic lyrics or ghazalīyāt in alphabetic order by the poet Fayz̤ī (d. 1004/1595).</p>
                        <p>Colophon (f. 333v): completed Thursday afternoon (date omitted).</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
